# **🧠 3.1 — What is Scope?**

Scope determines where variables are accessible in your code. Think of scope as a boundary or container that controls variable visibility.

```
text
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    SCOPE IN JAVASCRIPT                       │
│                                                             │
│  Scope = The "area" where a variable can be accessed        │
│                                                             │
│  3 Types:                                                   │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │
│  │ 1. Global Scope    — Accessible everywhere          │    │
│  │ 2. Function Scope  — Accessible inside function     │    │
│  │ 3. Block Scope     — Accessible inside { } block    │    │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**🔹 Global Scope**

```
var globalVar = "I am global";
let globalLet = "I am also global";
const globalConst = "Me too";

function test() {
    console.log(globalVar);    // ✅ Accessible
    console.log(globalLet);    // ✅ Accessible
    console.log(globalConst);  // ✅ Accessible
}

test();
console.log(globalVar);       // ✅ Accessible
/*
Output:
I am global
I am also global
Me too
I am global
*/
```

Why? Variables declared outside any function or block live in the Global Scope. They are accessible from anywhere in the program.

**🔹 Function Scope**

```
function greet() {
    var message = "Hello from inside!";
    let count = 10;
    const name = "Rahul";

    console.log(message);  // ✅ Accessible
    console.log(count);    // ✅ Accessible
    console.log(name);     // ✅ Accessible
}

greet();
console.log(message);      // ❌ ReferenceError: message is not defined
/*
Output:
Hello from inside!
10
Rahul
ReferenceError: message is not defined
*/
```

Why? Variables declared inside a function are trapped inside that function. Outside world cannot see them.

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              GLOBAL SCOPE                    │
│                                              │
│   ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐   │
│   │         FUNCTION SCOPE (greet)       │   │
│   │                                      │   │
│   │   var message = "Hello from inside!" │   │
│   │   let count = 10                     │   │
│   │   const name = "Rahul"               │   │
│   │                                      │   │
│   │   ✅ All accessible HERE             │   │
│   └──────────────────────────────────────┘   │
│                                              │
│   ❌ message, count, name NOT accessible     │
│      out here in global scope                │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**🔹 Block Scope**

```
if (true) {
    var a = 10;     // Function scoped (leaks out!)
    let b = 20;     // Block scoped (stays inside)
    const c = 30;   // Block scoped (stays inside)
}

console.log(a);     // ✅ 10 (var ignores block scope)
console.log(b);     // ❌ ReferenceError
console.log(c);     // ❌ ReferenceError
text
Output:
10
ReferenceError: b is not defined

```

Critical Understanding:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              BLOCK SCOPE RULES                      │
│                                                     │
│   var  → Does NOT respect block scope               │
│          Only respects function scope               │
│                                                     │
│   let  → RESPECTS block scope ✅                    │
│                                                     │
│   const→ RESPECTS block scope ✅                    │
│                                                     │
│   Block = any { } including if, for, while, etc.    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

```

**🔹 Nested Scope Example**

```
