setTimeout(function() {
    console.log("2");
}, 0);

Promise.resolve().then(function() {
    console.log("3");
});

console.log("4");
Step-by-step trace:
text
Step 1: console.log("1") → Execute → Print "1"

Step 2: setTimeout(fn, 0) → Register with Web API → callback to MACROTASK queue

Step 3: Promise.resolve().then(fn) → Promise resolves immediately
        → .then callback goes to MICROTASK queue

Step 4: console.log("4") → Execute → Print "4"

Step 5: Call stack is EMPTY
        → Event loop checks MICROTASK queue first (higher priority!)
        → Execute: console.log("3") → Print "3"

Step 6: Microtask queue is empty
        → Event loop checks MACROTASK queue
        → Execute: console.log("2") → Print "2"

