Why this order?
- "Start" and "End" are synchronous
- Promise 1's .then and Promise 3's .then are both queued as microtasks
- Promise 1 executes first (queued first)
- Promise 3 executes next (was already queued)
- Promise 2 executes last (queued only after Promise 1's callback returned)

Example 5: The Classic Interview Question
JavaScript
