1. console.log("script start") → SYNC → Print "script start"

2. setTimeout registers callback → MACROTASK queue

3. async1() is called:
   - console.log("async1 start") → SYNC → Print "async1 start"
   - await async2() → calls async2()
     - console.log("async2") → SYNC → Print "async2"
   - Everything AFTER await goes to MICROTASK queue
     (console.log("async1 end") is queued as microtask)

4. new Promise(executor):
   - executor runs SYNCHRONOUSLY
   - console.log("promise1") → SYNC → Print "promise1"
   - resolve() is called
   - .then callback goes to MICROTASK queue

5. console.log("script end") → SYNC → Print "script end"

6. CALL STACK EMPTY — Process microtasks:
   - console.log("async1 end") → Print "async1 end"
   - console.log("promise2") → Print "promise2"

7. Process macrotasks:
   - console.log("setTimeout") → Print "setTimeout"
