Step 3 received: 20
Final: 25
text
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  PROMISE CHAINING RULES                                      │
│                                                              │
│  1. .then() ALWAYS returns a new Promise                     │
│  2. If you return a VALUE from .then(), the next .then()     │
│     receives that value                                      │
│  3. If you return a PROMISE from .then(), the next .then()   │
│     waits for it to resolve and receives its value           │
│  4. If you throw an ERROR, it skips to .catch()              │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Refactoring Callback Hell with Promises:
