# Phase 4: Next.js and Advanced Frontend Concepts

## 📚 Section 1: Next.js Fundamentals

### 🎯 1.1 Understanding Next.js

```
/*
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                    WHAT IS NEXT.JS?                           ║
╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                               ║
║  Next.js is a React framework that provides:                  ║
║                                                               ║
║  • Server-Side Rendering (SSR)                                ║
║  • Static Site Generation (SSG)                               ║
║  • Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR)                      ║
║  • API Routes (Backend functionality)                         ║
║  • File-based Routing                                         ║
║  • Image Optimization                                         ║
║  • Built-in CSS/Sass support                                  ║
║  • TypeScript support out of the box                          ║
║  • React Server Components (App Router)                       ║
║                                                               ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

RENDERING STRATEGIES COMPARISON:

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    CLIENT-SIDE RENDERING (CSR)                  │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Browser                          Server                        │
│    │                                │                           │
│    │──── Request HTML ─────────────>│                           │
│    │<─── Empty HTML + JS bundle ────│                           │
│    │                                │                           │
│    │ [JS executes, fetches data]    │                           │
│    │                                │                           │
│    │──── API Request ──────────────>│                           │
│    │<─── JSON Data ─────────────────│                           │
│    │                                │                           │
│    │ [Render complete page]         │                           │
│                                                                 │
│  ❌ Poor SEO (empty initial HTML)                               │
│  ❌ Slow First Contentful Paint                                 │
│  ✅ Rich interactivity after load                               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  SERVER-SIDE RENDERING (SSR)                    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Browser                          Server                        │
│    │                                │                           │
│    │──── Request Page ─────────────>│                           │
│    │                                │ [Fetch data]              │
│    │                                │ [Render HTML]             │
│    │<─── Complete HTML + JS ────────│                           │
│    │                                │                           │
│    │ [Hydrate - make interactive]   │                           │
│                                                                 │
│  ✅ Great SEO (complete HTML)                                   │
│  ✅ Fast First Contentful Paint                                 │
│  ⚠️  Server load on each request                                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                 STATIC SITE GENERATION (SSG)                    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Build Time                       Runtime                       │
│    │                                │                           │
│    │ [Fetch data]                   │                           │
│    │ [Generate HTML]                │                           │
│    │ [Store static files]           │                           │
│    │                                │                           │
│                                   Browser                       │
│                                     │                           │
│                                     │──── Request ──────> CDN   │
│                                     │<─── Cached HTML ─── CDN   │
│                                                                 │
│  ✅ Fastest possible delivery (CDN)                             │
│  ✅ Great SEO                                                   │
│  ⚠️  Data can become stale                                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│           INCREMENTAL STATIC REGENERATION (ISR)                 │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                                 │
│  Combines benefits of SSG + SSR:                                │
│                                                                 │
│  1. Serve static page from cache                                │
│  2. In background, regenerate page after revalidation time      │
│  3. Next request gets fresh page                                │
│                                                                 │
│  ✅ Fast delivery (cached)                                      │
│  ✅ Fresh data (revalidation)                                   │
│  ✅ Great SEO                                                   │
│  ✅ Reduced server load                                         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
*/
```

### 🎯 1.2 Project Structure (App Router -

```
my-next-app/
├── app/                          # App Router (Next.js 13+)
│   ├── layout.tsx                # Root layout (required)
│   ├── page.tsx                  # Home page (/)
│   ├── loading.tsx               # Loading UI
│   ├── error.tsx                 # Error UI
│   ├── not-found.tsx             # 404 page
│   ├── global-error.tsx          # Global error boundary
│   │
│   ├── about/                    # /about route
│   │   └── page.tsx
│   │
│   ├── blog/                     # /blog route
│   │   ├── page.tsx              # /blog
│   │   ├── [slug]/               # Dynamic route
│   │   │   ├── page.tsx          # /blog/[slug]
│   │   │   └── loading.tsx       # Loading for this route
│   │   └── [...catchAll]/        # Catch-all route
│   │       └── page.tsx          # /blog/a/b/c
│   │
│   ├── (marketing)/              # Route group (no URL impact)
│   │   ├── layout.tsx            # Shared layout for group
│   │   ├── pricing/
│   │   │   └── page.tsx
│   │   └── features/
│   │       └── page.tsx
│   │
│   ├── @modal/                   # Parallel route (named slot)
│   │   └── login/
│   │       └── page.tsx
│   │
│   ├── api/                      # API routes
│   │   ├── route.ts              # /api (GET, POST, etc.)
│   │   └── users/
│   │       ├── route.ts          # /api/users
│   │       └── [id]/
│   │           └── route.ts      # /api/users/[id]
│   │
│   └── _components/              # Private folder (not routed)
│       └── Header.tsx
│
├── components/                   # Shared components
├── lib/                          # Utility functions
├── hooks/                        # Custom hooks
├── types/                        # TypeScript types
├── public/                       # Static assets
├── styles/                       # Global styles
│
├── middleware.ts                 # Middleware
├── next.config.js                # Next.js configuration
├── tailwind.config.js            # Tailwind configuration
└── tsconfig.json
```

### 🎯 1.3 Basic Routing

```
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// PAGE COMPONENT (app/page.tsx)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/page.tsx - Home page (/)
export default function HomePage() {
    return (
        <main>
            <h1>Welcome to My App</h1>
            <p>This is the home page</p>
        </main>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// LAYOUT COMPONENT (app/layout.tsx)
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/layout.tsx - Root layout (required)
import type { Metadata } from 'next';
import { Inter } from 'next/font/google';
import './globals.css';

const inter = Inter({ subsets: ['latin'] });

export const metadata: Metadata = {
    title: 'My Next.js App',
    description: 'Built with Next.js 14',
};

export default function RootLayout({
    children,
}: {
    children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
    return (
        <html lang="en">
            <body className={inter.className}>
                <header>
                    <nav>
                        <a href="/">Home</a>
                        <a href="/about">About</a>
                        <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
                    </nav>
                </header>
                <main>{children}</main>
                <footer>
                    <p>© 2024 My App</p>
                </footer>
            </body>
        </html>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// NESTED LAYOUTS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/blog/layout.tsx - Layout for all blog pages
export default function BlogLayout({
    children,
}: {
    children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
    return (
        <div className="blog-layout">
            <aside className="sidebar">
                <h3>Categories</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/blog?category=tech">Tech</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/blog?category=lifestyle">Lifestyle</a></li>
                </ul>
            </aside>
            <article className="content">
                {children}
            </article>
        </div>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// DYNAMIC ROUTES
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/blog/[slug]/page.tsx
interface BlogPostPageProps {
    params: { slug: string };
    searchParams: { [key: string]: string | string[] | undefined };
}

export default function BlogPostPage({ params, searchParams }: BlogPostPageProps) {
    const { slug } = params;

    return (
        <article>
            <h1>Blog Post: {slug}</h1>
            <p>Search params: {JSON.stringify(searchParams)}</p>
        </article>
    );
}

// Generate static params for SSG
export async function generateStaticParams() {
    const posts = await fetch('https://api.example.com/posts').then(r => r.json());

    return posts.map((post: { slug: string }) => ({
        slug: post.slug,
    }));
}

// Generate metadata dynamically
export async function generateMetadata({ params }: BlogPostPageProps): Promise<Metadata> {
    const post = await getPost(params.slug);

    return {
        title: post.title,
        description: post.excerpt,
        openGraph: {
            title: post.title,
            description: post.excerpt,
            images: [post.coverImage],
        },
    };
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// CATCH-ALL ROUTES
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/docs/[...slug]/page.tsx
// Matches: /docs/a, /docs/a/b, /docs/a/b/c, etc.
interface DocsPageProps {
    params: { slug: string[] };
}

export default function DocsPage({ params }: DocsPageProps) {
    const { slug } = params;
    // slug = ['a', 'b', 'c'] for /docs/a/b/c

    return (
        <div>
            <h1>Documentation</h1>
            <p>Path: {slug.join('/')}</p>
        </div>
    );
}

// Optional catch-all: app/docs/[[...slug]]/page.tsx
// Also matches: /docs (slug is undefined)

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// ROUTE GROUPS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/(marketing)/layout.tsx
// Routes in (marketing) share this layout but (marketing) is not in URL
export default function MarketingLayout({
    children,
}: {
    children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
    return (
        <div className="marketing-layout">
            <header className="marketing-header">
                {/* Marketing-specific header */}
            </header>
            {children}
        </div>
    );
}

// app/(dashboard)/layout.tsx
// Separate layout for dashboard routes
export default function DashboardLayout({
    children,
}: {
    children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
    return (
        <div className="dashboard-layout">
            <aside className="dashboard-sidebar">
                {/* Dashboard navigation */}
            </aside>
            <main className="dashboard-main">
                {children}
            </main>
        </div>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// PARALLEL ROUTES
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/layout.tsx with parallel routes
export default function Layout({
    children,
    modal,
    analytics,
}: {
    children: React.ReactNode;
    modal: React.ReactNode;      // @modal slot
    analytics: React.ReactNode;  // @analytics slot
}) {
    return (
        <html>
            <body>
                {children}
                {modal}
                {analytics}
            </body>
        </html>
    );
}

// app/@modal/login/page.tsx - Rendered in modal slot
export default function LoginModal() {
    return (
        <div className="modal-overlay">
            <div className="modal">
                <h2>Login</h2>
                <form>
                    <input type="email" placeholder="Email" />
                    <input type="password" placeholder="Password" />
                    <button type="submit">Login</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    );
}

// app/@modal/default.tsx - Default when no modal is active
export default function Default() {
    return null;
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// INTERCEPTING ROUTES
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

/*
Intercepting routes allow you to load a route within the current layout
while the URL changes. Useful for modals.

Convention:
- (.)  - Match same level
- (..) - Match one level above
- (..)(..) - Match two levels above
- (...) - Match from root
*/

// File structure for photo modal:
// app/
//   @modal/
//     (..)photo/[id]/
//       page.tsx          <- Intercepts /photo/[id] in modal
//   photo/
//     [id]/
//       page.tsx          <- Full page view (direct navigation)

// app/@modal/(..)photo/[id]/page.tsx
export default function PhotoModal({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
    return (
        <div className="modal-overlay">
            <div className="modal">
                <img src={`/photos/${params.id}.jpg`} alt={`Photo ${params.id}`} />
            </div>
        </div>
    );
}

// app/photo/[id]/page.tsx - Full page (when accessed directly)
export default function PhotoPage({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
    return (
        <div className="photo-page">
            <img src={`/photos/${params.id}.jpg`} alt={`Photo ${params.id}`} />
            <div className="photo-details">
                {/* Full photo details */}
            </div>
        </div>
    );
}
```

## 📚 Section 2: Server Components vs Client Components

```
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// SERVER COMPONENTS VS CLIENT COMPONENTS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

/*
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║              SERVER COMPONENTS (Default)                      ║
╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                               ║
║  ✅ Can directly access backend resources (DB, filesystem)   ║
║  ✅ Keep sensitive data on server (API keys, tokens)         ║
║  ✅ Reduce client-side JavaScript bundle                     ║
║  ✅ Automatic code splitting                                  ║
║  ✅ Streaming and Suspense support                           ║
║                                                               ║
║  ❌ Cannot use useState, useEffect, or other React hooks     ║
║  ❌ Cannot use browser APIs (window, document)               ║
║  ❌ Cannot use event handlers (onClick, onChange)            ║
║  ❌ Cannot use Context (client-side)                         ║
║                                                               ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║              CLIENT COMPONENTS ('use client')                 ║
╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                               ║
║  ✅ Can use React hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.)          ║
║  ✅ Can use event handlers (onClick, onChange, etc.)         ║
║  ✅ Can use browser APIs                                      ║
║  ✅ Can use Context                                           ║
║  ✅ Full interactivity                                        ║
║                                                               ║
║  ❌ Increases JavaScript bundle size                         ║
║  ❌ Cannot directly import Server Components                  ║
║  ❌ Data fetching requires API calls or props                 ║
║                                                               ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMPONENT TREE VISUALIZATION:

         ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
         │          Root Layout                │
         │       (Server Component)            │
         └─────────────────┬───────────────────┘
                           │
         ┌─────────────────┴───────────────────┐
         │                                     │
    ┌────▼────┐                         ┌──────▼──────┐
    │  Page   │                         │   Sidebar   │
    │(Server) │                         │  (Server)   │
    └────┬────┘                         └──────┬──────┘
         │                                     │
    ┌────▼────┐                         ┌──────▼──────┐
    │ Article │                         │  SearchBox  │
    │(Server) │                         │  (Client)   │
    └────┬────┘                         └─────────────┘
         │
    ┌────▼────┐
    │Comments │
    │(Client) │
    └─────────┘

Key: Server Components can render Client Components as children,
     but Client Components cannot import Server Components.
*/

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// SERVER COMPONENT EXAMPLE
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/posts/page.tsx (Server Component - default)
import { db } from '@/lib/db';

// This runs on the server - can access database directly
export default async function PostsPage() {
    // Direct database access - no API needed!
    const posts = await db.post.findMany({
        include: { author: true },
        orderBy: { createdAt: 'desc' },
    });

    return (
        <div>
            <h1>All Posts</h1>
            {posts.map(post => (
                <article key={post.id}>
                    <h2>{post.title}</h2>
                    <p>By {post.author.name}</p>
                    <p>{post.excerpt}</p>
                </article>
            ))}
        </div>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// CLIENT COMPONENT EXAMPLE
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// components/Counter.tsx
'use client'; // This directive makes it a Client Component

import { useState } from 'react';

export default function Counter() {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

    return (
        <div>
            <p>Count: {count}</p>
            <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>
                Increment
            </button>
        </div>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// MIXING SERVER AND CLIENT COMPONENTS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// Pattern 1: Server Component renders Client Component
// app/page.tsx (Server)
import Counter from '@/components/Counter';
import { db } from '@/lib/db';

export default async function Page() {
    const data = await db.settings.findFirst();

    return (
        <div>
            <h1>Dashboard</h1>
            {/* Pass server data as props to client component */}
            <Counter initialCount={data?.defaultCount ?? 0} />
        </div>
    );
}

// components/Counter.tsx (Client)
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';

interface CounterProps {
    initialCount?: number;
}

export default function Counter({ initialCount = 0 }: CounterProps) {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(initialCount);

    return (
        <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>
            Count: {count}
        </button>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// PASSING SERVER COMPONENTS AS CHILDREN
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// components/ClientWrapper.tsx
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';

interface ClientWrapperProps {
    children: React.ReactNode;
}

export default function ClientWrapper({ children }: ClientWrapperProps) {
    const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);

    return (
        <div>
            <button onClick={() => setIsOpen(!isOpen)}>
                {isOpen ? 'Hide' : 'Show'} Content
            </button>
            {isOpen && (
                <div className="content">
                    {children} {/* Server Component can be passed as children */}
                </div>
            )}
        </div>
    );
}

// app/page.tsx (Server)
import ClientWrapper from '@/components/ClientWrapper';
import ServerContent from '@/components/ServerContent';

export default function Page() {
    return (
        <ClientWrapper>
            {/* ServerContent is rendered on server, passed as children */}
            <ServerContent />
        </ClientWrapper>
    );
}

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// COMPOSITION PATTERNS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// ❌ WRONG: Client Component importing Server Component
// components/ClientComponent.tsx
'use client';

// This won't work!
// import ServerComponent from './ServerComponent';

// ✅ CORRECT: Pass Server Component as prop or children
// components/Modal.tsx
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';

interface ModalProps {
    trigger: React.ReactNode;
    content: React.ReactNode; // Server component passed as prop
}

export function Modal({ trigger, content }: ModalProps) {
    const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);

    return (
        <>
            <div onClick={() => setIsOpen(true)}>{trigger}</div>
            {isOpen && (
                <div className="modal-overlay" onClick={() => setIsOpen(false)}>
                    <div className="modal-content" onClick={e => e.stopPropagation()}>
                        {content}
                    </div>
                </div>
            )}
        </>
    );
}

// app/page.tsx
import { Modal } from '@/components/Modal';
import ProductDetails from '@/components/ProductDetails'; // Server Component

export default function Page() {
    return (
        <Modal
            trigger={<button>View Details</button>}
            content={<ProductDetails productId="123" />}
        />
    );
}

```

### 🎯 2.2 When to Use Each

```
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// DECISION GUIDE: SERVER VS CLIENT COMPONENTS
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

/*
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                    USE SERVER COMPONENTS FOR:                 ║
╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                               ║
║  • Data fetching (database, APIs, file system)                ║
║  • Accessing backend resources directly                       ║
║  • Keeping sensitive info on server (API keys, tokens)        ║
║  • Large dependencies (keep them off client bundle)           ║
║  • SEO-critical content                                       ║
║  • Static content that doesn't need interactivity             ║
║                                                               ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║                    USE CLIENT COMPONENTS FOR:                 ║
╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣
║                                                               ║
║  • Interactivity (onClick, onChange, etc.)                    ║
║  • State management (useState, useReducer)                    ║
║  • Effects (useEffect, useLayoutEffect)                       ║
║  • Browser APIs (localStorage, geolocation)                   ║
║  • Custom hooks that use state/effects                        ║
║  • Third-party components that need browser                   ║
║                                                               ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝
*/

// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: E-COMMERCE PRODUCT PAGE
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

// app/products/[id]/page.tsx (Server Component)
import { db } from '@/lib/db';
import { Suspense } from 'react';
import ProductDetails from '@/components/ProductDetails';
import AddToCartButton from '@/components/AddToCartButton';
import RelatedProducts from '@/components/RelatedProducts';
import ProductReviews from '@/components/ProductReviews';
import ProductSkeleton from '@/components/ProductSkeleton';

interface ProductPageProps {
    params: { id: string };
}

export default async function ProductPage({ params }: ProductPageProps) {
    // Server-side data fetching
    const product = await db.product.findUnique({
