### **Step 4: Key Technical Decisions**

```
text
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  TECHNICAL DECISIONS & REASONING                             │
│                                                              │
│  1. VIRTUALIZATION (react-window / react-virtuoso)           │
│     Why: Thousands of tweets → can't render all DOM nodes    │
│     How: Only render visible tweets + buffer                 │
│     Tradeoff: Complex scroll position management             │
│                                                              │
│  2. OPTIMISTIC UPDATES for Like/Retweet                      │
│     Why: Instant feedback improves UX                        │
│     How: Update UI immediately, sync with API in background  │
│     Rollback: If API fails, revert the UI change             │
│                                                              │
│  3. NEW TWEETS BANNER (not auto-insert)                      │
│     Why: Auto-inserting shifts content → bad UX              │
│     How: Buffer new tweets, show "X new tweets" banner       │
│     Click banner → prepend tweets and scroll to top          │
│                                                              │
│  4. IMAGE LAZY LOADING                                       │
│     Why: Most tweets have images → heavy bandwidth           │
│     How: IntersectionObserver + placeholder                  │
│     Progressive: Low-res blur → Full resolution              │
│                                                              │
│  5. CACHING STRATEGY                                         │
│     First load: API fetch → render → cache in IndexedDB      │
│     Subsequent: Show cached → fetch fresh → update           │
│     Offline: Show cached content with "offline" indicator    │
│                                                              │
│  6. WEBSOCKET for Real-time                                  │
│     Why: Polling is wasteful for real-time feed              │
│     How: Single WebSocket connection for all events          │
│     Reconnection: Exponential backoff on disconnect          │
│     Fallback: Long polling if WebSocket unavailable          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### **Step 5: Performance Optimizations**

```
text
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATIONS                                   │
│                                                              │
│  Rendering:                                                  │
│  • Virtualized list (render only visible items)              │
